  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/68620445/dynamodb-transactions-how-to-use-the-result-of-a-getitem-in-the-next-putitem",
  "title" : "DynamoDB Transactions: How to use the result of a GetItem in the next PutItem",
  "body" : "<p>Is it possible in DynamoDB Transactions to:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Update an item in table A (increment the value of an item to be specific to my scenario)</li>\n<li>Use the updated value of the attribute in a PutItem to another table B.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The transaction should preserve atomicity - so they should either succeed or fail as a unit.\nHow can I achieve this?</p>\n"
}